The paper deals with a document ranking problem, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The problem involves selecting documents based on user interests and topic coverage, which suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of approximation algorithms also suggests a connection to theoretical computer science (cs.SI).
